To simulate the effects of membrane depolarization, k
leak was increased by Δk
leak. According to , this would instantaneously increase the rate of Ca2+ entry by Δk
leak(ci − co). For example, this could describe rapid activation of non-inactivating Ca2+ channels in the case where permeation occurs at steady membrane potential and conforms with constant field theory with ci << co (Friel 1995). In this case, Δk
